# Cursor AI Assistant Rules for Blues Dance Festival Finder

## Project Context
- Full-stack web application for discovering blues dance festivals
- Tech stack: Next.js 14+, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, PostgreSQL, Prisma
- Focus on mobile-first design and performance optimization

## Code Style & Standards
- Use TypeScript for all JavaScript code
- Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations
- Use functional components with React hooks
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## File Organization
- Components in `/src/components/` with co-located styles if needed
- API routes in `/src/app/api/`
- Types in `/src/types/`
- Utilities in `/src/lib/`
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions

## Component Guidelines
- Create reusable UI components
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement proper TypeScript interfaces
- Include proper error handling and loading states
- Follow accessibility best practices

## Database & API
- Use Prisma for database operations
- Follow RESTful API conventions
- Implement proper error handling
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Include input validation and sanitization

## Performance
- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use lazy loading where appropriate
- Minimize bundle size

## Testing
- Write unit tests for utilities and business logic
- Include component tests for critical UI components
- Test API endpoints thoroughly

## Security
- Never expose sensitive environment variables
- Implement proper authentication and authorization
- Validate all user inputs
- Follow security best practices for web applications